{"author":{"id":"9d6b1353af19b52756ee62dbb13391155db8ecb7a8f1c579fb573e3059ffb150"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1672849012,"nonce":"ob8hh37PPCE8nTHgqYDTp6inpMg=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5ajcsw","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5031","origin":"github"},"title":"Add tool Decontaminator","message":"Decontaminator is a deep learning helping tool that filters out phage or fungi contigs from plant virome RNAseq assemblies. To be used standalone or with VirHunter.\n\nThis tool has no publication but is associated with this publication: \"VirHunter: A Deep Learning-Based Method for Detection of Novel RNA Viruses in Plant Sequencing Data\". Frontiers in bioinformatics. https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fbinf.2022.867111 Using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and a Random Forest Classifier, Virhunter aims to identify viruses in sequencing datasets.\n\nThis tool was tested with planemo (planemo lint, planemo test and planemo serve).","files":null}]}